Abstract = {In recent years, narrative visualization has gained much attention.
   Researchers have proposed different design spaces for various narrative
   visualization genres and scenarios to facilitate the creation process.
   As users' needs grow and automation technologies advance, increasingly
   more tools have been designed and developed. In this study, we
   summarized six genres of narrative visualization (annotated charts,
   infographics, timelines \& storylines, data comics, scrollytelling \&
   slideshow, and data videos) based on previous research and four types of
   tools (design spaces, authoring tools, ML/AI-supported tools and
   ML/AI-generator tools) based on the intelligence and automation level of
