Abstract = {Knowledge graphs are becoming increasingly popular for organizing and
   managing knowledge across various industries and academic fields.
   Knowledge graphs assist users to better understand domain knowledge by
   reorganizing and aggregating information. In the application scenario,
   recent research has mainly focused on constructing knowledge graphs to
   create narrative visualizations from the perspective of humanities
   expert, but the mapping relationship between knowledge graphs and
   narrative scripts which visualization designers specialize in remains
   largely unexplored. This paper aims to explore the use of cultural
   heritage knowledge graphs for producing narrative scripts that
   creatively preserve and communicate cultural heritage. To achieve this,
   the researchers constructed an ethnic costumes knowledge graph based on
   data collected from the Chinese National Museums of Ethnology and a
   literature survey. We conducted an experiment to identify typical
