Year = {2022},
Volume = {16},
Pages = {2821-2842},
Abstract = {News outlets are increasingly developing formats dedicated to capturing
   audience attention in social platforms. Meanwhile, the use of
   data-driven storytelling is becoming increasingly integrated into the
   ever-complex business models of news outlets, generating more impact and
   visibility. Previous studies have focused on studying these two effects
   separately. To fill this literature gap, this study identifies and
   analyzes the use of data journalism on social media content of AJ Labs,
   the team dedicated to producing data-driven and interactive stories for
   the Al Jazeera news network. Drawing upon a mixed-method approach, this
   study examines the use and characteristics of data stories on Instagram.
   Results suggest that there is reliance on producing visual content that
   covers topics such as politics and violence. In general, AJ Labs relies
